.SH NAME
SDL_GetAndroidExternalStorageState \- Get the current state of external storage for this Android application\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_system\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "Uint32 SDL_GetAndroidExternalStorageState(void);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The current state of external storage, a bitmask of these values:

.BR
.BR SDL_ANDROID_EXTERNAL_STORAGE_READ
,

.BR
.BR SDL_ANDROID_EXTERNAL_STORAGE_WRITE
\[char46]

If external storage is currently unavailable, this will return 0\[char46]

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the current state of external storage, or 0 if external
storage is currently unavailable\[char46]

